; Accident severity levels (e.g., slight, serious, fatal) refer to the magnitude of harm or damage caused by the accident; 
; Driver experience levels (novice, intermediate, experienced) are based on the number of years of driving experience (less than 5 years for novice, 5-10 years for intermediate, and more than 10 years for experienced);
; Vehicle categories (passenger_vehicle, commercial_vehicle, other) are based on the type of vehicle involved (e.g., automobile, lorry).
